not having a good computer or being able to make calls to my friends. I am lucky enough to have been able to come to Australia. However, despite the opportunities Australia offers, my community still struggles with connectivity on a daily basis, as Fiji relies on an ageing copper-based network.

The challenges of access and affordability in Fiji prevented me from finishing a degree on a scholarship to Australia. Without a sufficient internet connection, I had no choice but to drop out of university (University of the South Pacific).

I was without work for four months until I started a programme with a fellow based in Melbourne. As the digital marketing manager, my role is to advertise his company’s services and get him more clients. What I’ve come to realise is that digital platforms are the best platforms to find work in the modern world.

It is a global arena. It doesn’t matter where you are located. It’s a dynamic market where anyone can work virtually and have clients from anywhere. I have seen this dynamic everywhere in the world. From the United States of America to the United Kingdom, from the Caribbean to Latin America, it exists.

There are platforms that make transactions fast, available, and feasible; with global citizenship, and internet connection, you access a global pool of jobs. Online platforms, such as Upwork, Fiverr, and Freelancer, allow clients and freelance developers, writers, artists, and marketers to work together.
